Common Array methods used in Java

0. Declare an Array:
  int[] a = new int[5];
  int[] b = {1, 2, 3};
  int[] c = new int[]{1, 2, 3};
  
1. print an Array:
  String s = Arrays.toString(a);
  
2. Create an Array to an ArrayList:
  ArrayList<Integer> b = new ArrayList<Integer>(Arrays.aslist(a));
  
7. Convert an ArrayList to an Array
  Integer[] arr = new Integer[al.size()]; 
        arr = al.toArray(arr);
  
3. Contains:
  boolean b = Arrays.asList(a).contains(3);
  
4. Cancatenate two Arrays:
  // apache commons lang library
  int[] c = ArrayUtils.addAll(a, b);
  
5. Declare an array inline:
  method(new String[]{"a", "b", "c"});    // takes a new array as an argument
  
6. join an Array to a single string:
  // apache commons lang library
  String j = StringUtils.join(new String[]{"a", "b", "c"}, ",");
  
8. Convert an array to a set:
  Set<String> set = new HashSet<String>(Arrays.asList(a));

9. Reverse an array:
  ArrayUtils.reverse(a);
  
10. Remove element of an array:
// Array cannot add/delete, size does not change
// apache commons lang library
  int[] removed = ArrayUtils.removeElement(a, 3);
  
